Irbesartan tablets may be administered with other antihypertensive agents and with or without food.
The recommended initial dose of irbesartan tablets are 150 mg once daily. The dosage can be increased to a maximum dose of 300 mg once daily as needed to control blood pressure [see Clinical Studies].
The recommended dose is 300 mg once daily [see Clinical Studies].
The recommended initial dose is 75 mg once daily in patients with depletion of intravascular volume or salt (e.g., patients treated vigorously with diuretics or on hemodialysis) [see WARNINGS AND PRECAUTIONS].
